Many students of the Kaduna State College of Education, Gidan Waya, Jema’a Local Government Area of Kaduna State, were on Monday shot by security operatives, SaharaReporters has gathered.  The students were protesting over hike in school fees, when the security operatives made attempts to use to force to disperse them.  “We came out to protest over the increase of school fees when we met security operatives outside. They started shooting us, some of our colleagues are dead now,” a student told SaharaReporters.  He added that some students were also arrested and taken away by the police.